==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pessary
<hw>Pes"sa*ry</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧s"s⟦adot⟧*r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Pessaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>pessarium</ets>, <ets>pessum</ets>, <ets>pessus</ets>, Gr.
<grk>pesso`s</grk>: cf. F. <ets>pessaire</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An instrument or device to be introduced into and worn
in the vagina, to support the uterus, or remedy a malposition.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A medicinal substance in the form of a bolus or mass,
designed for introduction into the vagina; a vaginal
suppository.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pessimal</ent>⟦br⟧
